WRITING.TEXT:
 In all languages I know Math.random() (or the quivalent) returns a random number between 0 and 1 (while 0 is inclusive and 1 is exclusive). So a function could be like this:

    function randomInt(min, max) {
        return Math.floor(Math.random() * (max - min)) + max;
    }

If you happen to use it on many places throughout your code it may be a good idea to make a function like this and reuse it. But if you only need it at one place it may not be worth the hassle to extract it into a function.

In general your school is right though you should write the same code as less as possible at best only once, so you need to change it at as few places as possible. But in reality that is not always possible.
